results.name: Decimal expansion of sum_(n=1..infinity) (-1)^(n-1)*H(n)/n^2, where H(n) is the n-th harmonic number.
link: Philippe Flajolet, Bruno Salvy, Euler Sums and Contour Integral Representations, Experimental Mathematics 7:1 (1998), page 32.
xref: Cf. A002117: zeta(3); A197070: 3*zeta(3)/4; A233091: 7*zeta(3)/8; A076788: alternating sum with denominator n; A152648: non-alternating sum with denominator n^2; A152649: non-alternating sum with denominator n^3; A233033: alternating sum with denominator n^3.
